				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'll venture a guess and say that A0-A3 are used to distinguish between PPU rendering and $2007 accesses.  If the PPU is rendering, then A0-A2 should remain constant and A3 toggle between 0 and 1 during the course of the CHR fetches.  If $2007 were used, then A0-A2 would not be constant (if VRAM increment is 1) or A3 would not toggle (if VRAM increment is 32).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

