						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Or does the chip just decode one line for tiles from a pattern table, and all lines for the other pattern table, assuming the game will put this to good use (like the MMC3 with its scanline counter) ?</div>
<br />
<br />Presumably, this is how it works. Since both pattern tables have the same bank size, this doesn't present any real difficulty on the code side (with the MMC3, they added the extra bit to specify which one got two 2KBs and which one got four 1KBs).</div>

					
