						<div class="postbody">Okay, this still bothers me a bit. I think I fully understand how nametable latches works. When a tile is encountered horizontally, it just change the VROM bank used for BG, and this has proved to be very usefull to have up to 512 tiles at one time on a single BG screen, especially for letters in textboxes. (Punchout does just do one change midframe, that could be done on any maper. However, it does this thing to show the opponant's graphics before the fight, and the MMC4 games uses this a lot).
<br />
<br />But for sprites, I really don't see much usage of this, and the games I checked seems to no use sprite latch switching in an evident way as they do for BG.</div>

					
