				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Wow !!
<br />It's so much a shame it's all in japanese !
<br />
<br />The system seems to rely on a pulse on the read line to activate the latches.
<br />A shematic on page 14 seems to proof that A0-A2 are used for fully decoding the adress only if A13 is low too. Also, this shematic show two flip flops in series, meaning that the actual latch will be actived after the second read, regardless if the second read is still in the $xfd0-$xfef section.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

